{"key":"processedPost-7242684","value":{"id":7242684,"first":7241734,"last":16872485,"when":1185886546,"utime":"07/31/07 03:55 PM","cleanedPost":"For those who think mushrooms are going to respond to 'nutes' like plants, try mixing some plant food such as miracle gro into plain vermiculite or perlite and see how many mushrooms you grow.  Mycelium consumes its food, not drinks it. <br />Many growers over the years have experimented by adding plant food to substrates.  There's no noticeable effect.<br />Coir may have no 'nutes' for plants, but it has plenty of <i>food</i> for mushrooms.<br />RR"}}